            <a name="usage"/>
            <subsection name="JPBC Usage">
                <p>
                    To use jPBC it is enough to add to your classpath the following jars:
                    <ol type="1">
                        <li>
                            <font style="font-weight: bold;color:red"><tt>jpbc_1.3.0-api.jar</tt></font>
                            and
                        </li>

                        <li>
                            <font style="font-weight: bold;color:red"><tt>jpbc_1.3.0-plaf.jar</tt></font>.
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                </p>
                <p>
                    Note that all these libraries can be found in the <tt>jars</tt> folder of the distro package.
                </p>
            </subsection>
            <subsection name="PBC Wrapper Usage">
                <p>
                    To use the PBC wrapper you must compile the shared library
                    that enables the communication between PBC and jPBC. Go
                    <a href="./docs/pbcwrapper.html">here</a>
                    for instructions on how to compile the shared library.
                    <br/>
                    Then, to use the wrapper include the following jars
                </p>
                <ol>
                    <li>
                        <font style="font-weight: bold;color:green"><tt>jpbc_1.3.0-pbc.jar</tt></font>
                        and
                    </li>

                    <li>
                        <font style="font-weight: bold;color:green"><tt>jna-3.1.0.jar</tt></font>.
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </subsection>
            <subsection name="Cryptosystems Usage">
                <p>
                    If you want to use the already implemented
                    <a href="schemes/schemes.html">pairing based crypto-systems</a>
                    include the following jars:
                </p>
                <ol>
                    <li>
                        <font style="font-weight: bold;color:green"><tt>jpbc_1.3.0-crypto.jar</tt></font>
                        and
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <font style="font-weight: bold;color:green"><tt>bcprov-jdk16-140.jar</tt></font>.
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </subsection>
